OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1776643375
OL,3,CBereaved Israeli and Palestinian
OL,4,Cfathers now call each other brother
OL,6,FThey say mutual respect and
OL,7,Funderstanding between their two
OL,8,Fpeoples is what is needed to bring the
OL,9,Fbrutal conflict to an end.
OL,11,F"One word is essential, without it
OL,12,Fnothing will happen, the word is
OL,13,Frespect," said Mr Elhanan.
OL,15,F"You have to be able to respect the
OL,16,Fguy next to you exactly as you want to
OL,17,Fbe respected, no more and no less and
OL,18,Fonce you achieve this, all the rest
OL,19,Fare technicalities."
OL,26,@sD@AOUuD@IO]wD@AOU{D@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1776643375
OL,3,CBereaved Israeli and Palestinian
OL,4,Cfathers now call each other brother
OL,6,FThis, he says, can be achieved by
OL,7,F"being brave, by telling the truth, by
OL,8,Flooking straight into your eyes, not
OL,9,Fbeing polite, not being not
OL,10,Fcontroversial, telling them from the
OL,11,Friver to the sea, everyone should be
OL,12,Ffree, everyone should be safe,
OL,13,Feveryone should be equal".
OL,15,F"It's the most difficult thing to
OL,16,Ftrust your killer, your occupier, who
OL,17,Fstole your land, your house, who
OL,18,Fkilled your daughter," Mr Aramin added.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@YO]wD@AOUzD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1776643375
OL,3,CBereaved Israeli and Palestinian
OL,4,Cfathers now call each other brother
OL,6,FBut he said learning about the
OL,7,F"humanity" of those he considered the
OL,8,F"enemy" has changed his perspective.
OL,10,FThe 57-year-old said it was not until
OL,11,Fhe met Mr Elhanan's father, an
OL,12,FAuschwitz survivor, that he understood
OL,13,Fthe horror of the Holocaust.
OL,15,FHe said when he first heard about the
OL,16,FSecond World War genocide he thought:
OL,17,F"I don't care, it's not me, I don't
OL,18,Fknow about anyone."
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@JO]pD@AOUpD@GO]yD@AOUzD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1776643375
OL,3,CBereaved Israeli and Palestinian
OL,4,Cfathers now call each other brother
OL,6,F"When you meet Rami's Father, it's
OL,7,Fhard, and he starts to talk to you
OL,8,Fabout before he go to the oven.
OL,10,F"Then you understand what's the name
OL,11,Fof the Holocaust."
OL,13,FMr Elhanan said some in his community
OL,14,Fclaim grief caused him to lose his
OL,15,Fmind.
OL,17,F"I lost many friends, I lost many
OL,18,Ffamily members," he said, but added:
OL,19,F"I get new family members, new
OL,20,Ffriends, and I'm not afraid anymore
OL,21,Fthe worst has already happened."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUsD@RO]yD@AOUzD@PO]{D@AOU}D@
OL,26,A`O]
